Same issue here -- When installing on ARMv7l platform:
pip install tensorflow-1.9.0rc0-cp34-none-linux_armv7l.whl
tensorflow-1.9.0rc0-cp34-none-linux_armv7l.whl is not a supported wheel on this platform.
My pep425 tags are as follows (thank you @yifeif!):
[('cp35', 'cp35m', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp35', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp35', 'none', 'linux_armv7l'),
('cp34', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp33', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp32', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'),
('py3', 'none', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp35', 'none', 'any'), ('cp3', 'none', 'any'), ('py35', 'none', 'any'),
('py3', 'none', 'any'), ('py34', 'none', 'any'), ('py33', 'none', 'any'), ('py32', 'none', 'any'),
('py31', 'none', 'any'), ('py30', 'none', 'any')]
Doesn't ('cp34', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l') match the wheel? The target OS is Rasbian stretch. The wheel is from [http://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Nightly/job/nightly-pi-python3/]. Many thanks for your input!

body:
Same issue here -- When installing on ARMv7l platform:
    `pip install tensorflow-1.9.0rc0-cp34-none-linux_armv7l.whl `
    _tensorflow-1.9.0rc0-cp34-none-linux_armv7l.whl is not a supported wheel on this platform._
My pep425 tags are as follows (thank you @yifeif!):
    _[('cp35', 'cp35m', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp35', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp35', 'none', 'linux_armv7l'),
     ('cp34', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp33', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp32', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l'), 
     ('py3', 'none', 'linux_armv7l'), ('cp35', 'none', 'any'), ('cp3', 'none', 'any'), ('py35', 'none', 'any'),
     ('py3', 'none', 'any'), ('py34', 'none', 'any'), ('py33', 'none', 'any'), ('py32', 'none', 'any'), 
     ('py31', 'none', 'any'), ('py30', 'none', 'any')]_
Doesn't ('cp34', 'abi3', 'linux_armv7l') match the wheel?  The target OS is Rasbian stretch.  The wheel is from [http://ci.tensorflow.org/view/Nightly/job/nightly-pi-python3/].  Many thanks for your input!
